<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06080215 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06080215 </ACCESS><LEADPARA>  The pilot of a Northwest Airlines DC-9 testified Thursday in Detroit that henever saw a warning sign or the taxiway &quot;hold line&quot; advising him to stopbefore his plane strayed onto a runway and into the path of another Northwestjet in heavy fog last December. The approaching Boeing 727, accelerating for atakeoff at more than 100 mph, struck the DC-9 in a fiery collision that killedeight and injured 21, all on board the DC-9. The testimony of WilliamLovelace, 52, captain of Flight 1482, concluded the second day of hearings bythe National Transportation Safety Board on how the accident occurred.Lovelace agreed with his co-pilot James Schifferns, 43, who testified earlierin the day, that they became disoriented at least twice in the swirling fog.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Front  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  DETROIT CRASH PILOTS BLAME SWIRLING FOG  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  National News in Brief  </MEMO><BYLINE>  Mercury News Wire Services  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910320  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Wednesday  </DAY><MONTH>  March  </MONTH><PG.COL>  4A  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  138  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Wednesday March 20, 199100080215,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>